From the shadows the feline dark colored lion continued to watch,
crimson optics peering out from the darkness. It had tracked the
canine to this location, but had not dared to go into the government
building itself after it. Not fear so much but an innate caution, in
bred and strong.

It began to circle around, watching the progress, tail swishing in the
subdued light of its position. Its stealth shielding flickered from
time to time, for brief moment revealing its location to anyone with
the right kind of equipment, but then closing allowing him to
disappear from sensors.

The strange thing is that there was no true IFF signature coming from
it, even when the shield dipped intermittently; there was no reading
of Maximal or Predacon, only Cybertronian.

The creature quietly padded further into the shadows, a growl
vibrating deep in its chest as it looked for the best place to watch .
. . or pounce!

